message:
Sorry to bother folks—I'm a bit stuck on a code review comment and want to make sure I respond correctly. In PR #842 (auth-service), the reviewer asked me to replace the early return with a guard clause + extracted function; the current code is:
```ts
if (!user) return null;
if (!user.isActive) return null;
const token = await mintToken(user.id);
return token;
```
They suggested:
```ts
const ensureActiveUser = (user?: User) => {
  if (!user || !user.isActive) throw new UnauthorizedError();
  return user;
};
const activeUser = ensureActiveUser(user);
return mintToken(activeUser.id);
```
Given this is an internal endpoint that currently returns `null` for unauthenticated, should I follow the refactor and also change behavior to throw `UnauthorizedError`, or keep the `null` response and just do the extraction?

